# Role Codes & Naming Conventions

## Available Roles

The application uses these role codes in the `AppRole` table:

| Role Code     | Display Name   | Description                                       |
|---------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| `EMPLOYEE`    | Employee       | Standard employee access, can view and endorse    |
| `TEAM_LEADER` | Team Leader    | Can nominate employees to become SMEs             |
| `COORDINATOR` | Coordinator    | Manages department SMEs (activate/deactivate/delete)|
| `MANAGEMENT`  | Management     | Manager role, access to analytics dashboard       |

## Usage in Code

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use exact role codes from database
roles.includes("MANAGEMENT")
roles.includes("TEAM_LEADER")
roles.includes("COORDINATOR")
roles.includes("EMPLOYEE")

// ❌ WRONG - These role codes don't exist
roles.includes("MANAGER")      // Use "MANAGEMENT"
roles.includes("TL")           // Use "TEAM_LEADER"
roles.includes("ADMIN")        // Not a valid role
```

## Role Check Pattern

```typescript
// Server-side role check
const employee = await prisma.employee.findUnique({
  where: { email: session.user.email },
  include: {
    roles: { include: { role: true } },
  },
});

const roles = employee?.roles.map((er) => er.role.roleCode) ?? [];
const isManager = roles.includes("MANAGEMENT");
```

## Feature Access by Role

| Feature              | Route              | Required Role / Condition           |
|----------------------|--------------------|-------------------------------------|
| View Skills          | `/skills`          | All authenticated users             |
| View Experts/SMEs    | `/experts`         | All authenticated users             |
| Endorse SME Skills   | `/experts/[id]`    | All authenticated users             |
| Dashboard            | `/dashboard`       | `MANAGEMENT`                        |
| Nominate SMEs        | `/nominations`     | `TEAM_LEADER`                       |
| Department SMEs      | `/department-smes` | `COORDINATOR`                       |
| Create SME Profile   | `/sme-profile`     | Nominated employees (pending profile)|
| Edit SME Profile     | `/sme-profile`     | Existing SMEs                       |
